crates/ctx-cage is a self-contained crate providing an offline sandbox for running an untrusted agent under `bwrap`, plus the host-side services (billed API proxy, allowlisted tool broker) needed for a caged process to do real work. Depending on it means shelling out to one of its three binaries (`ctx-cage`, `ctx-run`, `ctx-cage-client`) — there is no library API meant for other crates to call directly.

The crate's real logic lives entirely in `src/`, whose entry point is `lifecycle::execute`; `Cargo.toml` just declares the lib+2-bin layout (a third bin, `ctx-cage-client`, is described in `src/rollup.ctx` but not separately called out in the manifest summary — check `Cargo.toml` before adding a fourth). `assets/` supplies two static payloads `src/` embeds or mounts verbatim: `cage-nsswitch.conf` (bind-mounted into the sandbox) and `cage-rules.md` (embedded via `include_str!` in `lib.rs` as `CAGE_RULES_MD` and passed to the caged `claude` process via `--append-system-prompt-file`). `cage-rules.md`'s claims about tool behavior (`ctx-access`, `ctx-verify`, `ctx-scan --update`) must track the real broker/tool implementations in `src/`; nothing enforces this automatically. `tests/` exercises `src/`'s public surface (`broker`, `bwrap`, `proxy`, `protocol`, `cli`, `summarize`) and pins the exact bwrap argv layout and in-cage path constants (`CAGE_BIN`, `CAGE_RULES_PATH`, `CAGE_RUN_DIR`) that `src/bwrap` defines — renaming any of these breaks tests in lockstep with the source.

Two independent egress models must stay distinct wherever this crate is touched: the OAuth/API-key proxy (`proxy.rs`, used by `lifecycle::run`) versus the allowlisted tool-broker (`broker.rs`+`protocol.rs`+`spawn.rs`, used by `lifecycle::serve`, with a wire format also spoken by `bin/ctx_cage_client.rs`). Billed-mode gating (`--allow-spend`/`CTX_CAGE_ALLOW_SPEND`) is checked independently in three places across `cli.rs` and `lifecycle`, so any change to which modes are "billed" needs verification in all three, not just the CLI.

No intent.md exists for this directory, so no divergence can be assessed.